{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Consensus threshold can be bypassed with duplicated signer entries","locations":["permissions/Consensus.sol:23","permissions/Consensus.sol:26","permissions/Consensus.sol:47"],"claim":"`checkSignatures` only enforces `signatures.length >= threshold` and validates each element independently; it never enforces signer uniqueness. The same authorized signer/signature can be repeated to satisfy threshold.","impact":"Multisig guarantees collapse for all `Consensus`-gated flows. Operations meant to require N distinct signers can be executed with fewer real signers, enabling unauthorized signature-queue deposits/redeems.","paths":["Configure threshold > 1 with at least one valid signer","Submit signatures array containing duplicate entries for that signer","`checkSignatures` returns true and privileged order executes"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Deposit cancellation uses oracle checkpoint value as Fenwick index","locations":["queues/DepositQueue.sol:107","queues/DepositQueue.sol:114"],"claim":"`cancelDepositRequest` reads `(exists, timestamp, index)` from `prices.latestCheckpoint()`, but for `Checkpoints.Trace224` the third return value is the checkpoint value (`priceD18`), not the request-tree index. That value is incorrectly used in `requests.modify(index, -assets)`.","impact":"Cancellations can revert (out-of-bounds Fenwick index) after reports exist, causing effective lockup of pending requests. In other states, subtraction may hit the wrong bucket and corrupt aggregate queue accounting.","paths":["User creates deposit request","Before claimability, user calls `cancelDepositRequest`","Function uses `priceD18` as Fenwick index in `requests.modify`, causing revert or wrong-bucket mutation"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Transfer whitelist check is inverted","locations":["managers/ShareManager.sol:138","managers/ShareManager.sol:139"],"claim":"With transfer whitelist enabled, `updateChecks` reverts when `from.canTransfer` is true or `to.canTransfer` is false. This inverts sender policy: non-transferable senders can pass if receiver is transferable, while transferable senders are blocked.","impact":"Transfer restriction policy is mis-enforced, allowing unauthorized transfers and blocking authorized ones.","paths":["Enable `hasTransferWhitelist`","Set sender `canTransfer=false` and recipient `canTransfer=true`","Sender transfer passes despite being non-transfer-whitelisted"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Signature queues bypass global queue pause","locations":["queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:11","queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:13","modules/ShareModule.sol:183"],"claim":"Standard deposit/redeem queues check `isPausedQueue(address(this))`, but signature queue entrypoints do not. Pausing a queue in `ShareModule` does not stop `SignatureDepositQueue.deposit` / `SignatureRedeemQueue.redeem`.","impact":"Emergency queue pause is ineffective for signature-based flows, allowing continued state-changing operations during incidents.","paths":["Admin pauses queue with `setQueueStatus(queue, true)`","User submits signature-queue order","Order still executes because entrypoint lacks pause check"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Auto-claim on token updates can become gas-prohibitive with many queues/assets","locations":["modules/ShareModule.sol:234","modules/ShareModule.sol:238","modules/ShareModule.sol:242","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:46","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:49","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:52"],"claim":"`claimShares` iterates all assets and all deposit queues. `TokenizedShareManager._update` calls `claimShares` for both `from` and `to` on every transfer/mint/burn, creating O(assets*queues) overhead per token movement.","impact":"As queue/asset count grows, ordinary share transfers can exceed gas limits and fail, creating liveness failures for tokenized share operations.","paths":["Protocol accumulates many assets/queues","Any transfer triggers `_update` -> `claimShares(from)` and `claimShares(to)`","Nested iteration and external queue calls make transfers revert from gas exhaustion"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Permissionless one-time `setVault` can be initialization-hijacked in non-atomic deployments","locations":["managers/ShareManager.sol:167","managers/RiskManager.sol:147","oracles/Oracle.sol:90","vaults/VaultConfigurator.sol:70"],"claim":"`setVault` is externally callable and only guarded by one-time initialization (`vault == 0`). If deployment/configuration is not atomic, an external caller can front-run and permanently bind a component to the wrong vault.","impact":"Initialization can be griefed or hijacked, potentially bricking intended deployment flows and forcing redeployments.","paths":["Component proxy is deployed with unset vault","Attacker calls `setVault(attackerVault)` first","Legitimate configurator call reverts with `InvalidInitialization`"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"VaultConfigurator.create Has No Access Control","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Configurator being permissionless is an expected factory pattern; this does not grant control over existing vaults or bypass role checks."},{"title":"Fee Calculation Can Overflow","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Fee math uses checked arithmetic plus `Math.mulDiv`; claimed overflow is not a practical protocol bug under Solidity 0.8 checks."},{"title":"VaultModule Missing Subvault Validation in Pull/Push Assets","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`_pullAssets/_pushAssets` call `riskManager.modifySubvaultBalance`, which enforces connected subvault validation via `requireValidSubvault`."},{"title":"SignatureQueue Price Validation Allows Price Manipulation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Order price is consensus-signed and then validated against oracle bounds; this is intended signed-order behavior, not an unconditional manipulation primitive."},{"title":"DepositQueue Deposit Can Be Front-Run","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Generic mempool visibility/MEV observation without a concrete protocol logic flaw."},{"title":"FeeRecipient Can Be Changed to Any Address","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Owner-controlled fee recipient is an expected governance trust assumption, not a vulnerability by itself."},{"title":"Consensus Allows Signature Replay Across Different Orders","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Signatures are bound to typed order hash; queue nonce checks prevent replay after execution."},{"title":"RiskManager convertToShares Can Revert on Invalid Price","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Reverting on suspicious/zero reports is intentional safety behavior, not a bug."},{"title":"BasicRedeemHook Potential Reentrancy in Loop","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Relevant external entrypoints are guarded with reentrancy protections; no concrete exploit path was substantiated."},{"title":"LidoDepositHook Unchecked Balance Change","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Hook uses reverting external calls (`safeIncreaseAllowance`, `wrap`, `withdraw`); balance-delta accounting is intentional."},{"title":"ShareModule getLiquidAssets Uses msg.sender Without Verification","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Function verifies caller is a registered redeem queue for the asset; no missing authorization found."},{"title":"Factory create Uses Predictable Salt","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Deterministic CREATE2 salt here does not yield a practical exploit; frontrunning cannot steal ownership/initialization semantics."},{"title":"TokenizedShareManager Auto-Claims Shares Without Access Control","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Not a standalone access-control issue; merged under gas/liveness finding for unbounded auto-claim costs."},{"title":"EigenLayerVerifier Incomplete delegateTo Verification","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Verifier validates call shape/roles; signature expiry semantics are enforced by downstream EigenLayer contracts."},{"title":"RiskManager Limit Check After State Modification","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Checks are performed before storage writes in the same transaction context; claimed race window is incorrect."},{"title":"ShareManager claimShares Can Be Called By Anyone","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Public claim-on-behalf is a benign helper pattern here; no concrete harmful state violation shown."},{"title":"BitmaskVerifier Bitmask Length Validation Bug","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`bitmask.length == data.length + 0x60` matches documented format (96-byte fixed segment plus calldata mask)."},{"title":"RedirectingDepositHook May Leave Assets Undeposited","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Partial allocation when limits are reached is expected behavior, not a correctness/security fault."},{"title":"FeeManager calculateFee Has No Access Control","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Public view fee calculation is not a security issue."},{"title":"ShareModule createQueue Does Not Verify Asset Supported by Oracle","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`createQueue` explicitly checks `IOracle($.oracle).isSupportedAsset(asset)` and oracle is initialized non-zero."},{"title":"Verifier setMerkleRoot Has Insufficient Access Control","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Role-based root updates are intentional; this is governance/key-management risk, not an implementation flaw."}]}
